WEBVTT

01:26.855 --> 01:28.657
GOOFY VOICE
<i>Welcome to the store.</i>

01:28.692 --> 01:30.494
<i>Are you a Busy Beaver?</i>

01:30.529 --> 01:33.794
No, I am not a Busy Beaver.

01:39.901 --> 01:41.868
<i>Are you a Frequent Beaver?</i>

01:41.903 --> 01:43.804
<i>Join our rewards club</i>
<i>for savings.</i>

01:43.839 --> 01:47.181
<i>You can get your teeth</i>
<i>into our dam good deals.</i>

01:53.387 --> 01:54.485
<i>Don't forget:</i>

01:54.520 --> 01:57.224
<i>If you need help, ask a Beaver.</i>

01:58.524 --> 02:00.722
Oh, oh!

02:00.757 --> 02:03.197
Hey. Oh, can I, uh, help you
with that, sir?

02:03.232 --> 02:06.200
Do you think
I don't know how to cut rope?

02:06.235 --> 02:08.697
No, it's just we usually do that
for ya.

02:08.732 --> 02:10.534
Do you think
I'm gonna cut myself

02:10.569 --> 02:12.833
and bleed all over your floor
and sue you?

02:15.167 --> 02:16.210
No.

02:16.245 --> 02:17.739
Then I don't need your help.

02:19.347 --> 02:20.709
Have an excellent day.

02:22.416 --> 02:24.680
<i>I'm a Busy Beaver.</i>

02:24.715 --> 02:26.176
Idiot.

02:27.388 --> 02:30.257
Did you, um, find everything

02:30.292 --> 02:32.490
you were lookin' for today?
Yes.

02:32.525 --> 02:33.458
Good.

02:34.956 --> 02:36.593
Let's see here.

02:40.126 --> 02:43.369
Uh, your total is 3.47.

02:43.404 --> 02:45.866
You charged me
for 6 feet of rope.

02:45.901 --> 02:48.539
Oh, yes, it's 99 cents a yard.

02:48.574 --> 02:52.202
I didn't get 2 yards.
I got 5 feet.

02:52.237 --> 02:54.578
Uh, yeah, we don't charge
by the foot.

02:54.613 --> 02:56.613
We charge by the yard.
99 cents a yard

02:56.648 --> 02:59.451
is 33 cents a foot,
times 5, that's 1.65.

02:59.486 --> 03:02.256
You charged me $1.98.

03:02.291 --> 03:03.917
You're good at math. Um...

03:03.952 --> 03:06.458
No, I know, but I can't put it
into the computer

03:06.493 --> 03:07.954
the way that you just said.

03:07.989 --> 03:11.793
What the hell kind of computer
can't do simple math?

03:11.828 --> 03:14.928
Can I speak to your manager?
He's at lunch.

03:14.963 --> 03:18.195
Lunch. All anyone cares about
these days is lunch.

03:18.230 --> 03:20.868
Is there anyone else in charge?
You want the assistant manager?

03:20.903 --> 03:22.474
Yes, I'd like
the assistant manager.

03:22.509 --> 03:23.442
'Kay.

03:25.578 --> 03:27.743
Hey, Taylor?

03:27.778 --> 03:29.910
Taylor? To the front register.

03:29.945 --> 03:32.814
What's up?
Oh, hey, Taylor.

03:32.849 --> 03:35.718
This is the assistant manager?
How old is she?

03:35.753 --> 03:37.423
Shouldn't you be in gym class?

03:37.458 --> 03:39.887
Sorry, what?
- Here. I got some change.

03:39.922 --> 03:42.593
Let me cover
that extra 33 cents for you.

03:42.628 --> 03:44.727
Sir, I do not want
your 33 cents.

03:44.762 --> 03:46.564
And this is not about 33 cents.

03:46.599 --> 03:48.929
This is about the fact
that I got 5 feet of rope

03:48.964 --> 03:50.469
because I want 5 feet of rope.

03:50.504 --> 03:51.965
And I shouldn't have to pay

03:52.000 --> 03:54.165
for 6 feet of rope
if I don't want 6 feet.

03:54.200 --> 03:56.442
Did you want
another foot of rope?

05:06.547 --> 05:07.744
Not again.

05:27.700 --> 05:29.766
How hard can this be?

05:56.256 --> 05:58.432
That bike goes over here.

05:58.467 --> 06:00.566
Hey! What the hell?

06:00.601 --> 06:02.260
That's mine.

06:02.295 --> 06:05.967
It belongs in the bike rack.
I was only gone half a minute.

06:06.002 --> 06:09.168
Next time, I'll lock it up
in the lost and found.

06:10.578 --> 06:13.040
Grumpy old bastard.

06:13.075 --> 06:14.173
Jeez.

06:27.661 --> 06:30.288
Not on the mirror. Mm.

06:31.929 --> 06:33.830
Hey, Otto!

06:39.937 --> 06:41.541
Okay.

07:06.293 --> 07:07.325
Hey!

07:34.156 --> 07:35.727
Don't you dare let
that little rat dog

07:35.762 --> 07:37.322
piss on my walkway again.

07:37.357 --> 07:38.961
I know it was you.
Ignore him, Prince.

07:38.996 --> 07:40.666
He's a nasty, bitter old man.

07:40.701 --> 07:42.327
And he has no idea
who's doing that.

07:42.362 --> 07:43.867
Well, it was one of you.

07:43.902 --> 07:46.298
And tell that useless boyfriend
of yours

07:46.333 --> 07:48.740
to stop stretching his groin
in public.

07:50.678 --> 07:53.140
Looks like a 14-year-old
Romanian gymnast,

07:53.175 --> 07:54.405
for God's sakes.

08:08.025 --> 08:10.058
Go on. Get outta here.

08:10.093 --> 08:11.422
Go.

08:50.001 --> 08:52.034
There he is,
the big man himself.

08:55.776 --> 08:57.270
What's all this?

08:57.305 --> 08:59.206
It's, well, retirement cake,
I guess.

08:59.241 --> 09:00.405
Call it what you like.

09:00.440 --> 09:02.308
"Have fun."

09:02.343 --> 09:05.047
"Have fun." Doing what?

09:05.082 --> 09:06.950
Well, have fun with
the rest of your life.

09:06.985 --> 09:09.084
We wanted to, you know...

09:09.119 --> 09:10.316
Celebrate?

09:10.351 --> 09:11.790
Yes! Well, no.

09:11.825 --> 09:13.286
Give you a nice send-off.

09:14.619 --> 09:17.059
"Nice."
Come on, Otto.

09:17.094 --> 09:19.094
You're the one
who decided to leave.

09:19.129 --> 09:22.262
And you did get
a nice severance package.

09:22.297 --> 09:24.429
You took me off Operations.

09:24.464 --> 09:26.299
You cut back on my hours.

09:26.334 --> 09:29.808
You made Terry,
who I trained, my supervisor.

09:29.843 --> 09:32.239
Terry, who can barely
figure out what year it is

09:32.274 --> 09:33.504
without his phone.

09:33.539 --> 09:36.683
So, yes,
I took the severance package.

09:36.718 --> 09:38.278
I'm sorry you see it that way.

09:38.313 --> 09:41.017
We all had to adjust
after the merger.

09:41.052 --> 09:43.085
But you've been quite an asset

09:43.120 --> 09:44.955
to this company
over the years, so--

09:44.990 --> 09:47.188
You have. Reliable as hell.

09:47.223 --> 09:49.091
We're gonna miss
those schedules of yours.

09:50.622 --> 09:52.523
To Otto!

09:52.558 --> 09:54.525
To Otto!

09:57.739 --> 10:00.872
Okay, Otto.
Want a piece of your face?

10:08.145 --> 10:09.749
Who's hungry?

10:12.677 --> 10:14.512
Look at this.

10:14.547 --> 10:16.217
No, no.

10:16.252 --> 10:18.450
Hey, hey, wait!
No, no, no.

10:18.485 --> 10:21.354
Hey, you cannot use this road
without a permit.

10:21.389 --> 10:24.060
I'm not parking.
I just dropped off a package.

10:24.095 --> 10:26.964
The sign doesn't say anything
about packages, does it?

10:26.999 --> 10:28.900
It says "permits"
and you don't have one.

10:28.935 --> 10:30.836
This is not a through street.

10:32.367 --> 10:33.872
Have a nice day, sir.

10:33.907 --> 10:35.302
Every time you come in here

10:35.337 --> 10:36.875
that means one of the residents

10:36.910 --> 10:38.910
can't park
in front of their homes!

10:38.945 --> 10:42.507
The other guys don't do this.
The guys with the white trucks.

10:42.542 --> 10:44.641
How come it's always
you brown guys?

10:44.676 --> 10:48.216
And I don't mean that racially!

10:54.554 --> 10:55.652
Hello.

10:55.687 --> 10:56.829
<i>Oh, hi.</i>

10:56.864 --> 10:58.226
<i>Sorry, can you hear me?</i>

10:58.261 --> 11:00.261
Yes.
<i>It's Susan.</i>

11:00.296 --> 11:02.428
Susan who?
<i>And I have great news</i>

11:02.463 --> 11:04.661
<i>about your health insurance.</i>
Oh, no, no, no.

11:04.696 --> 11:06.432
Robot, robot, robot!

11:09.734 --> 11:11.877
Well, who do I have to talk to

11:11.912 --> 11:13.912
to get this phone number
disconnected?

11:13.947 --> 11:16.046
- <i> That's Account Services.</i>
Can you transfer me

11:16.081 --> 11:17.443
or should I press a number?

11:20.415 --> 11:23.713
Well, I have been listening
to that music for seven minutes.

11:23.748 --> 11:25.517
<i>I do apologize, Mr. Anderson.</i>

11:25.552 --> 11:27.684
I would like the electricity
shut off at this residence.

11:27.719 --> 11:30.929
<i>Are you moving home?</i>
No, I am canceling the account.

11:30.964 --> 11:33.932
A-N-D-E-R-S-O-N.

11:33.967 --> 11:36.429
And why can't you refund me
for the six days?

11:36.464 --> 11:38.299
O-T-T-O.

11:38.334 --> 11:40.367
Oh, it's policy.
Well, my policy is

11:40.402 --> 11:42.875
that if I'm going to pay
for six days of gas,

11:42.910 --> 11:45.911
then I will use six days of gas.

11:45.946 --> 11:46.978
Then we are done here.

11:49.851 --> 11:50.916
Idiots.

13:06.818 --> 13:09.126
Okay.

13:09.161 --> 13:11.623
Go, go, go. Stop. Go.

13:11.658 --> 13:13.163
Okay. Yeah. Stop.

13:15.266 --> 13:18.069
Back. You're in the blind spot,
be careful. Use the Force.

13:18.104 --> 13:19.466
Oh, no, no, no.
Good, good.

13:19.501 --> 13:21.171
No, you're going
on the sidewalk. Okay.

13:22.911 --> 13:24.669
Back, back, back.

13:24.704 --> 13:25.670
Go away.

13:28.180 --> 13:29.982
Stop. Stop.

13:36.551 --> 13:37.550
Ah, shit.

13:37.585 --> 13:39.519
What the hell is he doing?

13:39.554 --> 13:43.259
Yes! Exactly! That's exactly
what I was saying.

13:43.294 --> 13:45.998
Hey, you can't just drive here.

13:46.033 --> 13:48.000
I'm not driving.
Am I driving the car? No.

13:48.035 --> 13:50.332
You can't just bring a car
on this street without a permit.

13:50.367 --> 13:53.599
No, we have a parking permit.
Right here. See?

13:53.634 --> 13:55.733
What the hell's it doing
in your pocket?!

13:55.768 --> 13:58.043
Well, I'm the driver.

13:58.078 --> 14:00.914
We're renting here. Yeah.

14:00.949 --> 14:01.981
In 206.

14:05.987 --> 14:08.053
That doesn't mean
you can back the trailer

14:08.088 --> 14:10.088
up to your front door.
No, I wasn't.

14:10.123 --> 14:12.926
I was, uh, parallel parking.

14:12.961 --> 14:14.290
Parallel to what?

14:16.228 --> 14:19.427
Yeah, that, uh...
That didn't go so well, huh?

14:19.462 --> 14:21.231
I'll just give it another try.

14:21.266 --> 14:22.826
Oh, my God.

14:25.105 --> 14:27.204
- Okay.
Hmm.

14:30.572 --> 14:31.802
Good. Good!

14:31.837 --> 14:34.112
MARISOL
Keep backing away.

14:34.147 --> 14:35.575
Now go away more.

14:35.610 --> 14:38.281
Okay, I got this.

14:38.316 --> 14:40.448
The other way,
but first the other way.

14:40.483 --> 14:41.746
- Easy.
<i>Exactamente.</i>

14:41.781 --> 14:43.781
Easy, easy.
Uh-huh, good.

14:43.816 --> 14:46.751
No. No, no. What? No!

14:46.786 --> 14:49.589
No, no, no! Stop!
Stop, stop, stop! Stop!

14:49.624 --> 14:52.130
Stop! Stop. Get outta the car.

14:52.165 --> 14:53.758
Get outta the car.
I'm sorry.

14:53.793 --> 14:55.397
How you could make it
this far through life

14:55.432 --> 14:56.893
without knowing
how to back up a trailer.

14:56.928 --> 14:59.434
My God, a dog with one front paw
and cataracts

14:59.469 --> 15:01.469
coulda done better than that.

15:01.504 --> 15:04.472
And an automatic, of course.
Give me the keys.

15:04.507 --> 15:06.606
Oh, they're in the cupholder.

15:06.641 --> 15:08.311
It's a push-button start.

15:08.346 --> 15:09.576
No, I knew that.

15:12.944 --> 15:14.416
What the hell is that?

15:14.451 --> 15:15.945
That's the radar.

15:15.980 --> 15:18.024
The trailer's too close
to the side of the car.

15:18.059 --> 15:19.916
That's why it's still beeping,
but--

15:19.951 --> 15:21.192
Okay.

15:23.460 --> 15:24.393
Hello.

15:27.233 --> 15:28.760
Hello.

15:28.795 --> 15:31.268
What's your name?
Otto.

15:31.303 --> 15:33.171
Otto?

15:33.206 --> 15:35.536
Otto. O-T-T-O.

15:36.671 --> 15:39.078
I'm Abbie, O-T-T-O.

15:40.312 --> 15:41.806
And I'm Luna.

15:43.216 --> 15:44.743
Nice to meet you.

16:02.400 --> 16:04.070
Oh, that was good, huh?

16:04.105 --> 16:06.666
He just did it
in one shot, huh?

16:08.901 --> 16:10.538
<i>Perfecto!</i>
Thank you, sir.

16:10.573 --> 16:13.178
Anyone who thinks
they need to use radar

16:13.213 --> 16:15.378
to back up a car shouldn't
be allowed to drive one.

16:15.413 --> 16:17.314
They shouldn't be allowed
to use the radio.

16:17.349 --> 16:19.008
That's what I said.

16:19.043 --> 16:21.010
And the permit goes on
the rearview mirror.

16:21.045 --> 16:22.913
Not in your pocket!
Okay, okay.

16:22.948 --> 16:24.321
Got it.
Bye! Thank you!

16:24.356 --> 16:27.720
Thank you, sir.
That was very nice. Wow.

16:31.363 --> 16:32.560
Idiot.

16:49.909 --> 16:52.283
You guys all ready?

16:52.318 --> 16:53.581
Okay.

16:57.158 --> 16:58.784
All right.

16:58.819 --> 17:01.050
Bring your stuff, okay?

17:01.085 --> 17:02.755
Come on, sweeties.

17:07.795 --> 17:09.960
<i>Chiquitita,</i> take your stuff.

17:45.668 --> 17:48.603
<i>How much more shelf space</i>
<i>is left?</i>

17:48.638 --> 17:50.242
<i>Three shelves.</i>

17:50.277 --> 17:51.903
How many more boxes of books
do you have?

17:51.938 --> 17:53.344
Seven or eight.

17:53.379 --> 17:55.313
"Then I'll build you
another bookcase."

17:55.348 --> 17:57.117
<i>Then I'll build you</i>
<i>another bookcase.</i>

18:13.630 --> 18:14.695
- Hi.
Hey.

18:14.730 --> 18:16.796
Hi. Otto.

18:16.831 --> 18:18.369
Right? Yes?

18:18.404 --> 18:20.206
Otto.

18:20.241 --> 18:22.604
Yeah, that's what I said.
No? What did I say--?

18:22.639 --> 18:25.376
It doesn't matter what you said.
Otto. O-T-T-O.

18:25.411 --> 18:27.510
Ah! Otto.
Otto.

18:27.545 --> 18:31.283
Oh, Otto. Okay, so it's the same
forward that is backwards.

18:31.318 --> 18:32.713
Otto.
It's Otto, Mari.

18:32.748 --> 18:35.045
It's just you don't hear
that name very often.

18:35.080 --> 18:36.486
I do.

18:36.521 --> 18:38.224
Okay. If we're interrupting,

18:38.259 --> 18:41.392
we can always come back.
What is it you want?

18:41.427 --> 18:43.724
I brought you some food.

18:43.759 --> 18:44.923
Why?

18:46.366 --> 18:47.794
Because you looked hungry.

18:47.829 --> 18:49.664
That's why we go
so well together.

18:49.699 --> 18:54.031
She loves to cook,
and I like to eat everything.

18:55.441 --> 18:57.804
Anyway, we just, uh...

18:57.839 --> 19:00.576
We wanted
to properly introduce ourselves

19:00.611 --> 19:03.348
because we're gonna be neighbors
and everything, so...

19:06.749 --> 19:07.880
So...
Okay.

19:07.915 --> 19:08.914
Okay.
Bye.

19:18.464 --> 19:20.233
My name is Marisol.

19:21.896 --> 19:23.302
And I'm Tommy.

19:25.933 --> 19:26.965
Otto.

19:29.277 --> 19:31.508
Are you always this unfriendly?

19:31.543 --> 19:33.939
I'm not unfriendly.

19:33.974 --> 19:35.413
I'd say
you're a little unfriendly.

19:35.448 --> 19:37.041
I'm not unfriendly.
<i>Un poquito.</i>

19:37.076 --> 19:39.285
I am not.
No? Okay, you're not.

19:39.320 --> 19:41.947
No, no, no, no.
You're not unfriendly.

19:41.982 --> 19:45.687
Every word you say
is like a warm cuddle.

19:45.722 --> 19:47.150
It really is.

19:49.055 --> 19:52.023
Enjoy it, heh.
What is it?

19:52.058 --> 19:54.025
Be careful with the salsa,
please.

19:54.060 --> 19:55.961
It's<i> pollo con mole.</i>

19:55.996 --> 19:57.732
It's really good.

19:57.767 --> 19:59.734
It's a Mexican dish.

19:59.769 --> 20:02.099
I'm Mexican.<i> Bueno, no.</i>

20:02.134 --> 20:06.136
I was born in El Salvador
because my father is from there.

20:06.171 --> 20:09.612
But my mom is Mexican, so we
went to first Mexico and then--

20:09.647 --> 20:12.879
And you?
I'm an IT consultant.

20:16.324 --> 20:17.752
Oh, I'm from Anaheim.

20:17.787 --> 20:19.050
Oh, from Anaheim.

20:19.085 --> 20:20.150
Anaheim, yeah.

20:20.185 --> 20:21.624
Yeah. El Paso.

20:23.188 --> 20:25.760
Okay, well, I have some things
I need to do.

20:25.795 --> 20:28.631
Excuse me, Mr. Otto. You
wouldn't have an Alvin wrench

20:28.666 --> 20:30.226
I could borrow, would you?

20:30.261 --> 20:31.799
You mean an Allen wrench.

20:31.834 --> 20:33.768
No, an Alvin wrench.

20:33.803 --> 20:35.572
It's Allen wrench.
- Allen wrench.

20:35.607 --> 20:37.739
It's "Allen" wrench, right?
It's Allen wrench.

20:37.774 --> 20:39.444
It's Alvin.
All morning,

20:39.479 --> 20:40.808
"Alvin wrench, Alvin wrench."

20:40.843 --> 20:42.172
Honey, it's Alvin, trust me.

20:42.207 --> 20:43.976
Everybody I know calls it
an Alvin wrench.

20:44.011 --> 20:46.682
Everybody you know is wrong.
Oh, yeah? You wanna Google it?

20:46.717 --> 20:49.421
My God.
Google it! Google it!

20:49.456 --> 20:51.654
Google it.
<i>Wikipediale. Wikipediale.</i>

20:51.689 --> 20:52.853
Give me your phone.

20:52.888 --> 20:55.460
No, my phone.
You use your phone.

21:02.326 --> 21:04.194
Do you know what size you need?

21:04.229 --> 21:05.965
Ah, just the usual size.

21:08.002 --> 21:09.672
Take the set.

21:09.707 --> 21:11.168
Thank you.
Aw, thank you.

21:11.203 --> 21:13.511
We go because you have
things to do, so...

21:22.555 --> 21:24.357
What do you want, huh?

21:41.233 --> 21:43.200
Mm! Hmm.

21:44.269 --> 21:45.235
Mmm.

22:00.956 --> 22:01.955
Mmm!

22:47.508 --> 22:49.706
OTTO'-
<i>Isn't she beautiful, son?</i>

22:49.741 --> 22:53.204
That's a Chevy engine for you.
Dependable.

22:53.239 --> 22:55.272
<i>Not enough you can depend on</i>
<i>in this world.</i>

22:55.307 --> 22:56.515
Dad, this is Otto.

22:59.850 --> 23:01.619
That's enough now, darling.

23:21.201 --> 23:23.707
Huh. Two for $8?

23:37.382 --> 23:39.855
Maybe I should just run myself
over with a car.

23:39.890 --> 23:41.494
Maybe that'll work.

23:41.529 --> 23:44.662
Found some of the flowers
you like.

23:44.697 --> 23:46.664
Pink.

23:46.699 --> 23:48.160
There was a deal on 'em.

23:49.328 --> 23:52.197
On sale. Two for 8 bucks.

23:54.300 --> 23:56.707
I'm sorry
I didn't get 'em here earlier.

23:58.304 --> 24:00.612
Got distracted.

24:00.647 --> 24:02.515
By some new neighbors.

24:05.014 --> 24:06.244
Nitwit husband.

24:08.050 --> 24:11.051
Didn't even know an Allen wrench
from one of the Chipmunks.

24:12.252 --> 24:14.527
Renters, of course.

24:16.828 --> 24:18.729
No commitment to anything.

24:20.832 --> 24:25.065
I know, I know. Maybe they can't
afford to buy yet.

24:25.100 --> 24:28.002
But what will they do
when those real estate bastards

24:28.037 --> 24:30.400
decide to tear down their house

24:30.435 --> 24:33.304
and put up more of those
ricky-ticky condos, huh?

24:33.339 --> 24:35.504
It's gonna happen.
I promise you.

24:35.539 --> 24:38.848
They're already driving
around the gates,

24:38.883 --> 24:41.114
driving right across the grass.

24:44.053 --> 24:45.822
Dye & Merika.

24:45.857 --> 24:48.088
What idiot thought
that was a good name

24:48.123 --> 24:50.486
for a real estate company?

24:50.521 --> 24:52.422
Sounds like "dying America."

24:55.130 --> 24:57.526
It is, of course.

24:57.561 --> 25:00.463
Can't even buy
a decent screw hook anymore.

25:01.807 --> 25:03.433
Or rope by the foot.

25:06.042 --> 25:07.943
Nothing works
when you're not home.

26:16.508 --> 26:17.441
<i>Next.</i>

26:21.788 --> 26:25.251
I suspect you have
hypertrophic cardiomyopathy,

26:25.286 --> 26:27.286
which is a genetic enlargement
of the--

26:27.321 --> 26:28.826
I know.

26:28.861 --> 26:30.454
My father had it.

26:32.799 --> 26:35.668
Well, you'll likely be around
a good long time,

26:35.703 --> 26:38.396
but I'm afraid your
military prospects end here.

26:40.070 --> 26:42.136
<i>Next.</i>

26:48.342 --> 26:50.276
One return ticket to Pittsburgh,
please.

26:50.311 --> 26:51.981
That'll be 1.10.

26:54.051 --> 26:55.479
Thank you.

27:01.894 --> 27:03.487
Coming through.

27:25.577 --> 27:27.918
Hey, you dropped your book!

27:27.953 --> 27:29.722
Miss, you dropped your book!
Hey!

28:16.397 --> 28:18.001
Is-- Is that mine?

28:19.103 --> 28:20.971
What?

28:21.006 --> 28:24.810
Yes. I saw you dropped it,
so I...

28:26.308 --> 28:29.276
Thank you so much.
I'm halfway through reading it.

28:29.311 --> 28:31.575
I would hate
not knowing how it ends.

28:33.821 --> 28:36.580
Oh, here. Why don't you join me?

28:41.356 --> 28:42.828
I'm Sonya.

28:42.863 --> 28:44.830
I'm Otto.

28:44.865 --> 28:46.799
It was my father's name.

28:46.834 --> 28:49.758
I'm on my way
to visit my father right now.

28:49.793 --> 28:51.331
I go every Thursday.

28:59.011 --> 29:01.440
Do you take this train a lot?

29:01.475 --> 29:05.114
Oh, no, I had to come into town
for my Army physical.

29:05.149 --> 29:07.017
Oh, God.

29:07.052 --> 29:08.579
Oh, that must be so hard,

29:08.614 --> 29:10.823
not knowing what
you're gonna face over there.

29:10.858 --> 29:13.320
When are you leaving?
I'm not--

29:15.291 --> 29:16.620
Not for a while.

29:18.657 --> 29:20.525
Tickets, please.

29:24.828 --> 29:26.795
Thank you.

29:26.830 --> 29:28.302
All right, thank you.

29:30.504 --> 29:32.306
I'm afraid
you're on the wrong train.

29:32.341 --> 29:34.077
This is an eastbound ticket.

29:36.081 --> 29:37.542
I must have, um...

29:38.886 --> 29:40.853
I'll get off
at the next station.

29:40.888 --> 29:42.954
Uh, how much is it?

29:42.989 --> 29:44.219
$1.75.

29:51.690 --> 29:52.689
One.

30:03.834 --> 30:05.845
Here. I have some change.

30:11.776 --> 30:13.017
Thank you.

30:17.683 --> 30:19.287
There you go.
Have a good day.

30:24.932 --> 30:26.096
A quarter to spare.

30:27.693 --> 30:29.231
It's 1964.

30:29.266 --> 30:31.233
It's pure silver.
Oh?

30:31.268 --> 30:33.598
Keep it, then. It's lucky.

30:38.143 --> 30:39.604
Yes, it is.

31:26.851 --> 31:30.292
Hey, Otto! A little late for
your morning rounds, isn't it?

31:30.327 --> 31:31.722
No.
No?

31:31.757 --> 31:33.427
Aren't you supposed to be
at work?

31:35.266 --> 31:37.002
No.
Oh. Cool.

31:37.037 --> 31:39.664
You wanna come over
for lunch, then?

31:39.699 --> 31:41.006
Lunch.

31:42.306 --> 31:44.669
Yeah.
No, no.

31:44.704 --> 31:47.639
Well, it's pork tenderloin,
in case you change your mind!

31:47.674 --> 31:49.113
No, no, no, no.

31:50.182 --> 31:51.676
Hey, excuse me.

31:53.977 --> 31:55.614
It was you.

31:55.649 --> 31:57.187
This is a private road,

31:57.222 --> 31:59.992
and these gates are to keep down
the flow of traffic.

32:00.027 --> 32:02.159
Not so idiot drivers
can go around them

32:02.194 --> 32:03.622
and tear up the grass.

32:03.657 --> 32:05.591
Okay. You got me.

32:05.626 --> 32:07.098
I'm with Dye & Merika.

32:07.133 --> 32:09.166
I'm gonna have
the groundskeeper come down

32:09.201 --> 32:11.465
and fix that up for ya, okay?
Good as new.

32:11.500 --> 32:13.797
Even better.
You have a good one now, okay?

32:13.832 --> 32:15.568
The rules are here
for a reason.

32:20.674 --> 32:22.212
I know what you guys are up to.

32:22.247 --> 32:25.149
Okay, Mr. Anderson.
Whatever you say.

32:25.184 --> 32:27.316
Keep up the neighborhood watch.

32:29.254 --> 32:32.651
Get out here, you little bugger!

32:34.160 --> 32:35.621
Come on. Yeah.

32:35.656 --> 32:37.293
Get out here!

32:37.328 --> 32:39.790
You throw one more rock,
and I swear I'll dropkick

32:39.825 --> 32:41.693
that little rat dog of yours
right over the roof.

32:41.728 --> 32:43.134
No, I'm not throwing it
at your house.

32:43.169 --> 32:44.861
That nasty cat scratched Prince.

32:44.896 --> 32:46.698
I'm gonna kill
that piece of shit.

32:46.733 --> 32:49.734
No, you're not.
What do you care? It's feral.

32:49.769 --> 32:52.308
It's probably full of all sorts
of disgusting diseases.

32:52.343 --> 32:55.674
So are you, most likely.
I don't throw rocks at you.

32:55.709 --> 32:57.478
Andy.
- What's up?

32:57.513 --> 32:59.579
Did you hear
what he just said this time?

32:59.614 --> 33:01.416
I told you before about
how he talks to me.

33:01.451 --> 33:04.881
Get outta here while you can.
I'm not your friend.

33:04.916 --> 33:06.982
Dye & Merika said they'll get
the old people on this street

33:07.017 --> 33:08.918
into a home.
The sooner the better!

33:26.971 --> 33:28.938
Hello.
What now?

33:28.973 --> 33:31.677
I just wanted
to bring the wrenches back.

33:31.712 --> 33:33.514
I found one
that came with the furniture.

33:33.549 --> 33:35.219
Congratulations.

33:35.254 --> 33:37.551
And I made you
some<i> salpores de arroz.</i>

33:37.586 --> 33:39.454
Is that chicken and mole?

33:39.489 --> 33:42.358
No. These are
Salvadoran cookies.

33:42.393 --> 33:44.019
They were my father's favorite,
so...

33:44.054 --> 33:45.889
They're delicious.
You're gonna love 'em.

33:45.924 --> 33:48.727
Yes, because I made them.
Also, Otto, I was wondering

33:48.762 --> 33:50.597
if you have a ladder
I can borrow.

33:50.632 --> 33:52.027
Our window is jammed.

33:52.062 --> 33:53.633
Why do you need a ladder?

33:53.668 --> 33:57.065
Well, it's the one up there.
It...

33:57.100 --> 33:58.605
It won't open.

33:58.640 --> 34:01.036
And you're gonna try to open it
from the outside?

34:01.071 --> 34:02.444
Yeah. Right.

34:03.744 --> 34:05.117
I'll get my coat.

34:05.152 --> 34:06.514
Okay. Thank you.

34:08.848 --> 34:12.223
I like how his hands are waving.
Let's put the arm in.

34:14.689 --> 34:15.919
Oh, good.
Anita.

34:15.954 --> 34:18.394
Otto, hate to bother you,

34:18.429 --> 34:20.264
but we don't have any heat.

34:20.299 --> 34:22.794
Um, could you come take a look?

34:22.829 --> 34:25.335
Try bleeding your radiators.

34:25.370 --> 34:27.733
How would I go about that?

34:27.768 --> 34:29.933
By bleeding the radiators.

34:29.968 --> 34:32.100
Otto. Don't be rude.

34:32.135 --> 34:34.476
I wasn't being rude.

34:34.511 --> 34:38.414
Well, it's hard to tell the
difference sometimes with Otto.

34:38.449 --> 34:40.284
Yeah.

34:40.319 --> 34:44.255
By the way,
we just moved to 206.

34:44.290 --> 34:46.015
I'm Marisol.
I'm Tommy.

34:46.050 --> 34:47.588
Oh, welcome, honey.
Nice meeting you.

34:47.623 --> 34:49.359
I'm Anita.

34:49.394 --> 34:52.428
My husband, Reuben, is the one
who used to handle the heat.

34:52.463 --> 34:53.957
Okay.
But we always knew

34:53.992 --> 34:56.630
a day would come when he
wouldn't be able to handle

34:56.665 --> 34:58.533
things around the house
any longer.

34:59.866 --> 35:01.800
Maybe Reuben should have
thought of that

35:01.835 --> 35:04.440
when he organized his coup.

35:04.475 --> 35:07.102
That was a long time ago.

35:07.137 --> 35:08.345
A coup?

35:08.380 --> 35:10.446
It was a misunderstanding.

35:10.481 --> 35:11.744
It was a coup.

35:14.177 --> 35:18.718
Otto, can't you just go breathe
Anita's radiators for her?

35:18.753 --> 35:21.622
No. Because you don't
breathe radiators.

35:21.657 --> 35:24.196
You bleed them.
Honey, look at this ramp.

35:24.231 --> 35:25.824
Oh, that's Sonya's.
We needed this for the trailer.

35:25.859 --> 35:28.200
Put that down. Put that down!

35:28.235 --> 35:30.466
Who said you could touch that?!
Oh, sorry.

35:30.501 --> 35:32.237
All of you get outta here.
Go, go.

35:32.272 --> 35:35.163
Take your ladder and go.
Get outta here. All of you.

35:35.198 --> 35:37.869
- Okay.
- Thank you.

35:37.904 --> 35:39.002
Thank you.
Watch out.

35:40.511 --> 35:42.709
Right. Right.

35:45.681 --> 35:47.681
BOTH
Thank you!

35:52.523 --> 35:55.227
No. What are you doing in here?

35:55.262 --> 35:57.185
How did you get in here?
Come on.

35:57.220 --> 35:59.693
Come on. Go! Get outta there.

36:01.224 --> 36:03.829
No, get out. Get out of there.

36:03.864 --> 36:05.028
Come on, go.

36:07.307 --> 36:08.603
Hey.

36:12.136 --> 36:14.246
Let go!

36:14.281 --> 36:15.379
Let go.

36:18.780 --> 36:21.748
You scratch me, I'll bite you.

36:24.885 --> 36:26.918
That'll teach you.

36:30.429 --> 36:31.923
Stupid cat.

36:36.633 --> 36:37.797
ABBIE &-
Hi, Otto!

36:39.097 --> 36:41.306
O-T-T-O.

36:58.325 --> 37:00.292
Otto. Um...

37:00.327 --> 37:02.085
I loaned you my garden hose
last August.

37:02.120 --> 37:05.022
If you give it back to me, I'll
bleed your radiators for you.

37:06.828 --> 37:08.157
Come in.

37:15.342 --> 37:18.233
So those new neighbors of yours,

37:18.268 --> 37:20.840
they seem quite lovely,
don't you think?

37:20.875 --> 37:24.316
Lovely.
Yeah, well, you may have

37:24.351 --> 37:27.319
some more new neighbors
soon enough.

37:27.354 --> 37:30.179
The realty people,
they've been telling us...

37:30.214 --> 37:34.249
Reuben and I have to move out.

37:34.284 --> 37:36.526
No, that's a load of crap.

37:36.561 --> 37:38.363
They don't own this house.
You do.

37:38.398 --> 37:40.761
Yeah, well, that's what I said.

37:40.796 --> 37:43.665
They have been talking
to our boy, Chris.

37:43.700 --> 37:45.469
Ugh!
Now he's saying

37:45.504 --> 37:47.867
that I can no longer
take care of Reuben,

37:47.902 --> 37:51.101
that he needs to be
in a special care place.

37:51.136 --> 37:54.940
And I should move
into a retirement home.

37:54.975 --> 37:56.711
What does Chris know about it?

37:56.746 --> 37:58.614
He's an idiot.
He always has been.

37:58.649 --> 38:00.550
They can't make you do anything.

38:03.390 --> 38:05.819
Does he even know we're here?

38:05.854 --> 38:07.150
Of course he does.

38:07.185 --> 38:09.020
Don't let him fool you.

38:09.055 --> 38:11.330
He's still in there.

38:13.400 --> 38:17.160
Um, let me go find your hose.

38:35.851 --> 38:39.347
The whole neighborhood
is falling apart these days.

38:39.382 --> 38:40.755
They don't even have

38:40.790 --> 38:42.625
a homeowners' association
anymore.

38:44.057 --> 38:47.124
No one left
to keep things running.

38:49.029 --> 38:50.369
Not like we did.

38:57.444 --> 38:59.037
Now, just to be clear...

39:00.139 --> 39:03.107
I still haven't forgiven you.

39:03.142 --> 39:06.484
I just didn't realize you would
fall to shit so quickly.

39:07.718 --> 39:10.378
And now...

39:10.413 --> 39:14.624
they're tearing apart everything
we worked so hard to build.

39:14.659 --> 39:18.221
I haven't even left yet,
and they're trying to erase us.

39:20.126 --> 39:25.261
Well, I am not staying around
to see that happen.

39:25.296 --> 39:26.603
I'm leaving.

39:28.002 --> 39:30.365
For good.
- Anita, ready for lunch?

39:30.400 --> 39:32.202
I'm making that creamed corn
you like.

39:32.237 --> 39:34.809
Oh, thank you.
Oh, thank you, Otto.

39:34.844 --> 39:37.042
I'm sorry it took so long
to give it back.

39:37.077 --> 39:38.483
Um, you wanna stay for lunch?

39:38.518 --> 39:40.375
Yeah, Anita made
a pork tenderloin.

39:40.410 --> 39:42.520
No, I have a lot of things
I have to do.

39:45.921 --> 39:49.087
Reuben, what are you doing, hon?

39:49.122 --> 39:51.155
Let go.
- What are you doing?

39:51.190 --> 39:54.422
Let go.
Reuben. Reuben.

39:54.457 --> 39:56.501
Let...
What are you doing?

39:56.536 --> 39:57.964
...go.

40:09.175 --> 40:10.240
Oh, man.

40:31.868 --> 40:34.572
Try opening it
from the inside a little.

40:36.070 --> 40:38.543
It's higher than I thought.

40:38.578 --> 40:40.578
I'm a little bit dizzy, honey.

41:20.620 --> 41:21.718
Hmm.

41:23.216 --> 41:24.479
Mmm.

41:24.514 --> 41:25.689
Mm...

41:50.650 --> 41:54.784
<i>♪ Sun through the shadows ♪</i>

41:54.819 --> 41:57.050
<i>♪ Light through the door ♪</i>

41:58.988 --> 42:00.988
<i>♪ Your voice like an echo ♪</i>

42:03.289 --> 42:05.487
<i>♪ I can't hear anymore ♪</i>

42:07.392 --> 42:09.458
<i>♪ So I follow your steps ♪</i>

42:09.493 --> 42:11.900
<i>♪ While the love</i>
<i>That you left ♪</i>

42:11.935 --> 42:13.803
<i>♪ Is burned in my heart ♪</i>

42:15.939 --> 42:18.071
<i>♪ With dreams in my mind ♪</i>

42:18.106 --> 42:23.439
<i>♪ The next time that</i>
<i>I have you in my arms ♪</i>

42:23.474 --> 42:29.885
<i>♪ 'Cause I will tell you</i>
<i>The whole truth ♪</i>

42:32.285 --> 42:34.626
<i>♪ There's no color ♪</i>

42:34.661 --> 42:37.629
<i>♪ In the world without you ♪</i>

42:44.869 --> 42:47.166
Looks like we'll both have
to take the next one.

42:49.302 --> 42:52.171
Otto.
It was your father's name.

42:52.206 --> 42:53.271
You remembered.

42:56.639 --> 42:58.980
Did you have to go back
to the military center?

42:59.015 --> 43:02.313
No, I wanted to pay you back
for the train ticket.

43:04.317 --> 43:07.516
Wouldn't it be nicer
if you invited me to dinner?

43:07.551 --> 43:12.026
<i>♪ The best gift of this life ♪</i>

43:12.061 --> 43:14.798
<i>♪ Is to see you up close... ♪</i>

43:17.803 --> 43:19.000
<i>Shall we?</i>

43:19.035 --> 43:21.002
Yeah, let's go in.

43:21.037 --> 43:22.135
You're...

43:22.170 --> 43:24.808
...fifteen minutes late.
Am I?

43:24.843 --> 43:26.942
<i>♪ So I write it all down ♪</i>

43:26.977 --> 43:29.208
<i>♪ All these moments</i>
<i>I've found ♪</i>

43:29.243 --> 43:31.650
<i>♪ Til I see you, my love ♪</i>

43:35.645 --> 43:38.888
So, what kinds of things
interest you?

43:40.353 --> 43:41.550
Interest me like...?

43:41.585 --> 43:43.893
What are you passionate about?

43:43.928 --> 43:46.060
Machines. Engines.

43:46.095 --> 43:47.556
I like knowing how things work.

43:47.591 --> 43:49.030
<i>I like knowing how things work.</i>

43:49.065 --> 43:51.736
What each part does
to make a car run smoothly.

43:51.771 --> 43:53.661
It's more complicated
than people realize.

43:53.696 --> 43:55.333
A carburetor has to mix
gas and air

43:55.368 --> 43:57.874
in just the right combination,
and then the spark plug

43:57.909 --> 44:00.470
has to ignite that mixture,
which drives the piston

44:00.505 --> 44:01.911
and the connecting rods
and the drive shaft--

44:01.946 --> 44:04.573
Where did you learn so much
about cars?

44:04.608 --> 44:06.674
From my father.

44:06.709 --> 44:09.347
It's all we really talked about.
He was a good dad.

44:10.757 --> 44:11.789
Dependable.

44:13.122 --> 44:14.517
He passed away.

44:15.795 --> 44:16.761
Two months ago.

44:19.128 --> 44:20.930
It was sudden.

44:20.965 --> 44:21.931
I'm sorry.

44:24.463 --> 44:26.430
And your mom?

44:26.465 --> 44:28.366
Don't remember her much.

44:28.401 --> 44:31.875
Just how it felt
when she was gone.

44:39.918 --> 44:41.753
Why didn't you get an entrée?

44:46.716 --> 44:48.221
I ate at home.

44:49.994 --> 44:51.125
Why?

44:52.898 --> 44:54.931
So you could order
whatever you wanted.

45:01.170 --> 45:03.632
Look, I lied to you.

45:03.667 --> 45:05.909
I'm sorry.

45:05.944 --> 45:08.879
I'm not in the Army.
I couldn't pass my physical.

45:08.914 --> 45:10.980
And if I had, at least
I'd have a job now,

45:11.015 --> 45:14.115
which is what I was counting on.
But I don't.

45:16.856 --> 45:19.087
And I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

45:20.926 --> 45:21.859
I should go.

45:39.978 --> 45:41.274
Otto!

45:48.382 --> 45:49.450
Otto!

45:52.518 --> 45:54.089
I'm coming.

45:54.124 --> 45:55.860
I'm coming!

45:55.895 --> 45:57.928
What? What do you want?

45:57.963 --> 46:00.128
What are you doing here?
What are you doing?

46:00.163 --> 46:02.130
I'm looking for you.
Well, you found me.

46:02.165 --> 46:04.759
Can you please take me
to the hospital? Please?

46:04.794 --> 46:07.498
Tommy fell off the ladder. The
ambulance just took him away.

46:07.533 --> 46:09.038
Well, you can drive yourself

46:09.073 --> 46:11.535
in that imported toaster
you call a car.

46:11.570 --> 46:13.306
I don't have a license.

46:13.341 --> 46:16.012
How old are you?
Eh? Thirty.

46:16.047 --> 46:18.014
And you don't have
a driver's license?

46:18.049 --> 46:20.214
I have a driving's permit.

46:20.249 --> 46:22.645
I just never got
to the other parts.

46:22.680 --> 46:24.647
How many other parts are there?

46:27.751 --> 46:28.816
Please!

46:28.851 --> 46:30.686
<i>Por favor.</i>

46:30.721 --> 46:33.557
Focus! Please, listen!

46:34.901 --> 46:36.560
Tommy is in the hospital,

46:36.595 --> 46:39.167
and he may be dying as we speak.

46:39.202 --> 46:41.235
So are you gonna drive me
to the hospital,

46:41.270 --> 46:43.303
or are you gonna
make me take a bus?

46:43.338 --> 46:45.536
I will drive you.
Thank you.

46:45.571 --> 46:46.944
Was it so hard?

46:48.541 --> 46:50.211
Where are you going?

46:50.246 --> 46:53.313
I'm going to get the children!

46:53.348 --> 46:55.216
The children?

47:00.927 --> 47:03.158
Pick me up, pick me up!

47:13.203 --> 47:15.302
Bam everywhere. No! No!

47:20.243 --> 47:21.572
Smack, smack, smack!

47:21.607 --> 47:23.541
These dolls.

47:23.576 --> 47:25.708
Are they some kind
of superheroes?

47:25.743 --> 47:28.282
Um,<i> luchador</i> are wrestlers.
Yeah.

47:29.384 --> 47:30.515
Wrestlers.

47:30.550 --> 47:32.781
I found a Mr. Bear book!
So I see.

47:34.422 --> 47:36.422
She wants you
to read to her.

47:37.755 --> 47:38.897
Exactly.

47:41.330 --> 47:43.429
