in your garage.

1:20:49.415 --> 1:20:53.087
That was, like,
excellent strategy.

1:20:53.122 --> 1:20:54.682
Good job.

1:20:58.589 --> 1:21:02.195
Otto, also, I was thinking
you've done so much for us.

1:21:02.230 --> 1:21:03.856
I wanna do something
for you too.

1:21:03.891 --> 1:21:05.198
I don't need anything.

1:21:05.233 --> 1:21:06.529
Well, I think you could do

1:21:06.564 --> 1:21:09.037
with some decent food.
Sometimes. No?

1:21:09.072 --> 1:21:11.798
Those cookies...
The what? The<i> "salporanz"?</i>

1:21:11.833 --> 1:21:14.900
Those are not bad.
They're not bad.

1:21:14.935 --> 1:21:16.473
And, also, I was thinking

1:21:16.508 --> 1:21:18.442
that I can help you
clean out your house

1:21:18.477 --> 1:21:20.983
and clean out the front hall
in your home,

1:21:21.018 --> 1:21:24.448
and help you pack the coats and
shoes you have there of Sonya's.

1:21:24.483 --> 1:21:26.384
That's not needed.

1:21:26.419 --> 1:21:29.585
No, but it can help you
move on.

1:21:29.620 --> 1:21:31.290
I don't wanna move on.

1:21:31.325 --> 1:21:33.226
She's always gonna be with you.

1:21:33.261 --> 1:21:35.327
But you're still here.

1:21:35.362 --> 1:21:36.592
That's enough.

1:21:38.002 --> 1:21:39.661
When my father died,

1:21:39.696 --> 1:21:41.663
my mother, she stopped living.

1:21:41.698 --> 1:21:44.765
She just stopped like she used--
Stop talking!

1:21:44.800 --> 1:21:47.273
Stop it.
Okay! Don't yell at me.

1:21:48.936 --> 1:21:53.642
Why can't people mind
their own business? Idiots.

1:21:53.677 --> 1:21:55.182
Interrupting me at every turn.

1:21:55.217 --> 1:21:57.184
The more they babble,
the more they drown out

1:21:57.219 --> 1:21:59.153
the memory of her voice.

1:21:59.188 --> 1:22:02.123
I don't want
to clear Sonya from my life.

1:22:02.158 --> 1:22:03.586
She was everything.

1:22:03.621 --> 1:22:05.027
There was nothing before her,

1:22:05.062 --> 1:22:07.293
and there's nothing after!

1:22:07.328 --> 1:22:08.723
I'm something.

1:22:12.465 --> 1:22:14.663
That son of a bitch!

1:22:14.698 --> 1:22:18.766
Uh-uh! No, no, no.
Ah-ah-ah! Ah-ah-ah!

1:22:18.801 --> 1:22:21.505
Stop right there.
You stop that car!

1:22:21.540 --> 1:22:23.540
Did you leave that gate open?

1:22:23.575 --> 1:22:25.344
You left that gate open,
didn't you?

1:22:25.379 --> 1:22:26.807
You're the only one
who gives a damn.

1:22:26.842 --> 1:22:28.776
I give a damn about people
following the rules.

1:22:28.811 --> 1:22:31.449
Yes, I know.
I know all about you.

1:22:31.484 --> 1:22:34.056
There's a file on you
at the office. It's this thick.

1:22:34.091 --> 1:22:35.783
I know about your wife.

1:22:35.818 --> 1:22:37.686
How you blame whatever happened
to her on everybody else.

1:22:37.721 --> 1:22:41.492
You shut up.
Don't you say one more word.

1:22:41.527 --> 1:22:44.660
Take it easy, Otto. Look,
I'm not trying to upset you,

1:22:44.695 --> 1:22:48.037
but you really shouldn't be
living alone.

1:22:48.072 --> 1:22:50.237
I mean, we know more about you

1:22:50.272 --> 1:22:52.800
than you probably realize, so...

1:22:52.835 --> 1:22:55.638
Just look after
that heart of yours, okay?

1:22:55.673 --> 1:22:57.640
What do you know about my heart?

1:22:57.675 --> 1:22:59.906
Hey, what do you know
about my heart?!

1:22:59.941 --> 1:23:01.974
You prying bastard!

1:23:02.009 --> 1:23:03.250
Otto, Otto.

1:23:03.285 --> 1:23:04.911
Otto, what's going on?

1:23:04.946 --> 1:23:07.155
Are you okay? Do you feel okay?

1:23:07.190 --> 1:23:09.586
You wanna help me,
close the gate.

1:23:23.030 --> 1:23:24.568
Otto. Otto.

1:23:25.802 --> 1:23:27.769
Otto.

1:23:30.411 --> 1:23:32.081
Otto.

1:23:32.116 --> 1:23:34.611
Talk to me, Otto. Please?

1:23:38.254 --> 1:23:40.914
Otto.<i> ¿Qué pasó?</i>

1:23:45.723 --> 1:23:47.261
Talk to me, Otto.

1:24:01.772 --> 1:24:02.936
Otto.

1:24:06.282 --> 1:24:07.578
Otto.

1:24:25.598 --> 1:24:26.927
Thank you.

1:24:56.563 --> 1:24:58.332
It'll be cute on you.

1:24:58.367 --> 1:24:59.993
