<i>♪ I should be hoping</i>
<i>But I can't stop thinking... ♪</i>

1:30:21.558 --> 1:30:22.821
Hi.

1:30:26.222 --> 1:30:27.859
There you are.

1:30:41.336 --> 1:30:45.943
<i>♪ Just make it go away ♪</i>

1:30:45.978 --> 1:30:47.978
<i>That's enough now, darling.</i>

1:30:51.984 --> 1:30:54.985
You're angry. I know.

1:30:57.154 --> 1:30:58.384
And sad.

1:31:00.157 --> 1:31:01.354
So am I.

1:31:03.666 --> 1:31:05.424
But now we have to live.

1:31:20.408 --> 1:31:21.880
What now?

1:31:27.382 --> 1:31:29.987
Malcolm.
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to--

1:31:30.022 --> 1:31:31.824
I'm not gonna shoot you.

1:31:31.859 --> 1:31:34.156
What was that noise?
Uh...

1:31:34.191 --> 1:31:36.158
The generator blew
and the power is out.

1:31:36.193 --> 1:31:39.425
What d'ya want? It's freezing.

1:31:39.460 --> 1:31:42.571
I was hoping you might let me
crash on your couch for a night.

1:31:42.606 --> 1:31:44.100
This is not a hotel.

1:31:45.939 --> 1:31:47.708
No. I'm sorry.

1:31:47.743 --> 1:31:49.369
Why can't you go home?

1:31:52.275 --> 1:31:53.813
My dad kicked me out.

1:31:59.216 --> 1:32:01.623
There's a sofa you can use.

1:32:01.658 --> 1:32:05.088
Don't go into the dining room.
The ceiling needs repair.

1:32:05.123 --> 1:32:07.255
It's upstairs
in Sonya's old study.

1:32:07.290 --> 1:32:10.126
So why did he kick you out?

1:32:10.161 --> 1:32:12.293
Because you're Malcolm now?

1:32:12.328 --> 1:32:14.394
Yeah, because I'm Malcolm.

1:32:14.429 --> 1:32:17.232
Because I dress like this.

1:32:17.267 --> 1:32:20.873
I read too much. I don't
like sports. Take your pick.

1:32:20.908 --> 1:32:23.106
He's embarrassed
'cause I'm trans.

1:32:23.141 --> 1:32:24.503
Then he's an idiot.

1:32:26.980 --> 1:32:28.309
This is you.

1:32:28.344 --> 1:32:30.080
Try not to touch anything.

1:32:30.115 --> 1:32:31.114
Okay.

1:33:30.912 --> 1:33:32.208
Well...

1:33:32.243 --> 1:33:34.045
Good morning.
The power's still out

1:33:34.080 --> 1:33:37.081
so I cooked up the last of the
eggs while they're still good.

1:33:38.249 --> 1:33:40.216
Hope you don't mind.

1:33:40.251 --> 1:33:42.053
I have to do my rounds.

1:33:42.088 --> 1:33:44.088
Don't you at least want
some coffee first?

1:33:46.587 --> 1:33:47.861
Yes.

1:33:54.199 --> 1:33:55.330
There you go.

1:33:56.696 --> 1:33:58.740
Uh, some eggs?

1:33:58.775 --> 1:34:00.665
I wouldn't say no.

1:34:00.700 --> 1:34:02.007
All right.

1:34:19.796 --> 1:34:20.960
That can...

1:34:22.293 --> 1:34:23.523
goes in here.

1:34:26.726 --> 1:34:27.967
Hang that up.

1:34:33.700 --> 1:34:36.107
Hey, Otto! Making your rounds.

1:34:36.142 --> 1:34:38.571
You mind if I join you?
I need to get my steps in.

1:34:38.606 --> 1:34:40.441
Okay.

1:34:40.476 --> 1:34:41.750
I'm Jimmy.
Malcolm.

1:34:41.785 --> 1:34:43.147
Nice to meet you.
Aw, thanks.

1:34:46.119 --> 1:34:47.514
Yes.

1:34:47.549 --> 1:34:49.890
Yes.

1:34:49.925 --> 1:34:51.617
Hey, Otto, if you want
to slow down,

1:34:51.652 --> 1:34:53.553
we can 'cause my beats are up.

1:34:53.588 --> 1:34:54.895
Yes.

1:35:08.603 --> 1:35:10.735
Otto, did you hear
they're moving Reuben

1:35:10.770 --> 1:35:12.704
into assisted living
this afternoon?

1:35:12.739 --> 1:35:13.947
Who is?

1:35:13.982 --> 1:35:15.982
The Dye & Merika guys.

1:35:16.017 --> 1:35:17.412
My God.

1:35:17.447 --> 1:35:19.744
They convinced Anita
to sell the house.

1:35:19.779 --> 1:35:21.746
No, they made the deal
with Chris.

1:35:21.781 --> 1:35:24.485
Chris? He can't do that.
Yeah, he can.

1:35:24.520 --> 1:35:27.752
After Dye & Merika found out
Anita had Parkinson's,

1:35:27.787 --> 1:35:29.798
they tracked Chris down and--

1:35:29.833 --> 1:35:30.997
Parkinson's?
Yeah.

1:35:31.032 --> 1:35:32.757
So last year
Chris convinced Anita

1:35:32.792 --> 1:35:35.430
to give him power of attorney
in case she got worse.

1:35:35.465 --> 1:35:38.499
So Dye & Merika made the deal
with Chris to buy the house.

1:35:38.534 --> 1:35:40.908
Those pricks.

1:35:40.943 --> 1:35:44.945
Wait, Anita found out
she had Parkinson's last year?

1:35:44.980 --> 1:35:46.111
No, that's not right.

1:35:46.146 --> 1:35:47.508
She would've told Sonya.

1:35:47.543 --> 1:35:48.883
Sonya would've told me.

1:35:50.150 --> 1:35:52.249
Well, Anita and Reuben

1:35:52.284 --> 1:35:53.954
didn't want
you and Sonya to know.

1:35:53.989 --> 1:35:56.825
They said you had enough
on your plate as it is.

1:35:58.455 --> 1:35:59.861
They said that?

1:36:10.830 --> 1:36:14.139
I need to see everything
you ever got from Dye & Merika.

1:36:14.174 --> 1:36:17.307
Notices, letters. Do you have
a copy of the power of attorney?

1:36:17.342 --> 1:36:19.012
How do you know about that?

1:36:19.047 --> 1:36:20.849
Do you have it?
Yes.

1:36:20.884 --> 1:36:22.015
Get it.
Yes.

1:36:23.645 --> 1:36:28.648
And any records
of Reuben's condition and yours.

1:36:28.683 --> 1:36:30.518
Did Jimmy tell you that?

1:36:30.553 --> 1:36:32.025
Can you get it now?

1:36:32.060 --> 1:36:33.092
Yes.

1:36:38.902 --> 1:36:40.495
I've been an idiot.

1:36:42.367 --> 1:36:44.334
I got so wrapped up
in my own troubles,

1:36:44.369 --> 1:36:46.006
I stopped thinking
of anyone else.

1:36:46.041 --> 1:36:48.206
And I figured
they weren't thinking about me.

1:36:49.946 --> 1:36:51.572
Friends shouldn't do that.

1:36:51.607 --> 1:36:52.672
So...

1:36:54.412 --> 1:36:56.885
This isn't easy to say
after all this time.

1:36:58.020 --> 1:36:59.382
But I'm sorry.

1:37:02.024 --> 1:37:04.420
And I will sort all this out.

1:37:17.138 --> 1:37:18.533
I need to use your phone.

1:37:20.570 --> 1:37:23.340
Why can't you use your own?

1:37:23.375 --> 1:37:25.243
Mine is disconnected
at the moment.

1:37:27.313 --> 1:37:29.775
Why?
That doesn't matter.

1:37:29.810 --> 1:37:31.810
I just need to use your phone,
okay?

1:37:33.913 --> 1:37:36.221
You know what? No.

1:37:36.256 --> 1:37:38.784
No?
No.

1:37:38.819 --> 1:37:41.589
You won't tell me
why your phone is disconnected?

1:37:41.624 --> 1:37:45.032
You won't tell me
why you need to use my phone?

1:37:45.067 --> 1:37:48.629
You won't tell me what happened
to you in the street yesterday?

1:37:48.664 --> 1:37:51.940
And then you went inside and
you wouldn't even open the door?

1:37:53.900 --> 1:37:55.603
You scared me, Otto.

1:37:57.244 --> 1:37:59.310
Do you know how long
I was out there?

1:37:59.345 --> 1:38:02.478
And I didn't know if something
had happened to you.

1:38:03.811 --> 1:38:06.449
Or if something
was gonna happen to you.

1:38:06.484 --> 1:38:10.618
And I'm sorry if I said the
wrong thing about Sonya's coats.

1:38:10.653 --> 1:38:13.390
But I was just trying to help.

1:38:13.425 --> 1:38:16.360
And you left me out there.

1:38:18.430 --> 1:38:21.167
So, no. You can't use my phone.

1:38:27.274 --> 1:38:30.638
You think your life is so hard
because everybody's an idiot

1:38:30.673 --> 1:38:33.014
and you have to do everything
on your own, right?

1:38:34.182 --> 1:38:35.181
Right?

1:38:36.349 --> 1:38:38.349
But guess what.

1:38:38.384 --> 1:38:39.647
You can't.

1:38:40.947 --> 1:38:42.056
No one can.

1:38:43.389 --> 1:38:45.158
And I think
you should just be happy

1:38:45.193 --> 1:38:48.953
that someone was trying to help
you get through a crappy day.

1:38:48.988 --> 1:38:50.526
Even if they're an idiot.

1:38:51.727 --> 1:38:54.134
So...
The real estate bastards

1:38:54.169 --> 1:38:57.830
are trying to force Anita
and Reuben out of their home.

1:38:57.865 --> 1:38:59.799
That's why
I need to use your phone.

1:39:03.211 --> 1:39:05.211
Okay, fine. Come on.

1:39:21.493 --> 1:39:23.658
We had never had a vacation.

1:39:27.730 --> 1:39:30.038
Sonya was six months pregnant.

1:39:30.073 --> 1:39:34.306
And she wanted to do something
special before the baby came.

1:39:34.341 --> 1:39:37.507
So we booked a trip
to Niagara Falls.

1:39:39.577 --> 1:39:41.412
On the way back,
the bus crashed.

1:39:43.119 --> 1:39:45.746
There'd been a recall
on the brake lines,

1:39:45.781 --> 1:39:47.946
but the company
never had them fixed.

1:39:49.521 --> 1:39:51.356
Sonya was paralyzed...

1:39:52.458 --> 1:39:54.590
and we lost our son.

1:39:58.398 --> 1:40:01.861
<i>After three months, she was</i>
<i>finally able to come home.</i>

1:40:01.896 --> 1:40:04.864
<i>But they had started building</i>
<i>the new condos</i>

1:40:04.899 --> 1:40:08.175
<i>and the community center</i>
<i>and the walkways,</i>

1:40:08.210 --> 1:40:12.179
<i>none of which were designed</i>
<i>for people in wheelchairs.</i>

1:40:12.214 --> 1:40:15.677
The builders could have
changed their plans.

1:40:15.712 --> 1:40:20.121
But the laws weren't in place
back then, and they didn't care.

1:40:20.156 --> 1:40:21.749
<i>I did.</i>

1:40:22.983 --> 1:40:25.291
<i>I cared.</i>

1:40:25.326 --> 1:40:28.129
And I was so angry.

1:40:28.164 --> 1:40:31.297
What does that mean? People
like her? What does that mean?

1:40:31.332 --> 1:40:34.465
What're you tryin' to say?!
Get off of me!

1:40:34.500 --> 1:40:36.533
That's when they voted me out

1:40:36.568 --> 1:40:38.766
as head
of the homeowners' association.

1:40:41.067 --> 1:40:43.144
I wanted to obliterate them all.

1:40:43.179 --> 1:40:44.805
The builders, and the realtors,

1:40:44.840 --> 1:40:46.972
and the bus company,
the bus driver.

1:40:47.007 --> 1:40:48.842
I never would have let it go...

1:40:50.351 --> 1:40:51.482
but for Sonya.

1:40:52.914 --> 1:40:54.753
Sonya said
we had to keep living.

1:40:57.820 --> 1:40:59.094
That's what I did.

1:41:00.526 --> 1:41:02.020
I lived for Sonya.

1:41:06.367 --> 1:41:08.895
Six months ago
she passed away.

1:41:08.930 --> 1:41:10.501
<i>Cancer.</i>

1:41:14.177 --> 1:41:15.638
I was going to join her.

1:41:17.312 --> 1:41:19.640
That's why I had them
disconnect my phone.

1:41:22.713 --> 1:41:26.220
But now I think
she wants me to keep living.

1:41:28.455 --> 1:41:32.457
And I have things to do.

1:42:03.182 --> 1:42:04.951
You're wasting your time, Otto.

1:42:04.986 --> 1:42:07.492
It's a done deal.
Reuben's coming with us.

1:42:07.527 --> 1:42:09.626
And if you get in our way,

1:42:09.661 --> 1:42:11.496
I'll have you arrested.

1:42:11.531 --> 1:42:15.302
I'm not doing a thing.
Don't you take another step.

1:42:15.337 --> 1:42:17.799
You are not taking my husband
away from me.

1:42:17.834 --> 1:42:21.374
Anita, please. We're doing this
for your own good.

1:42:21.409 --> 1:42:25.345
What you're doing is trying
to take my property.

1:42:25.380 --> 1:42:29.679
I want Reuben to stay right here
for the rest of his life

1:42:29.714 --> 1:42:31.681
with me in our home.

1:42:31.716 --> 1:42:34.354
Okay, but who's gonna
take care of Reuben

1:42:34.389 --> 1:42:35.916
when you're no longer able to?

1:42:35.951 --> 1:42:38.424
Who's gonna take care of you?
Otto?

1:42:38.459 --> 1:42:41.427
Otto's not in the best health
either. Are you, Otto?

1:42:42.595 --> 1:42:43.759
I'll take care of 'em.

1:42:45.092 --> 1:42:47.026
What are you doing?
Put that down.

1:42:47.061 --> 1:42:48.665
Anita and Reuben are
like family to me.

